<article>
    <h1>BLACK COM&#xAD;EDY NORDIC FILM FES&#xAD;TI&#xAD;VAL</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE WEEKEND</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Five films, one each from Den­mark, Fin­land, Ice­land, Nor­way and Swe­den, will be screened at The Pro­jec­tor.</p>
    <p>Among them is the Nor­we­gian black com­edy In Or­der Of Dis­ap­pear­ance (2014, M18,</p>
    <p>116 min­utes, Sun­day, 5.10pm), se­lected for the com­pe­ti­tion sec­tion of the 64th Ber­lin In­ter­na­tional Film Fes­ti­val. Nils (Stel­lan Skars­gard, right) is a snow­plough driver who dis­cov­ers his son dead from a drug over­dose. The mild-man­nered man’s per­son­al­ity changes and he be­comes a cold-blooded vig­i­lante hunt­ing mem­bers of a gang re­spon­si­ble for his son’s death.</p>
    <p>This movie was re­made in English as Cold Pur­suit (2019), with Liam Nee­son in the main role.</p>
    <p>WHERE The Pro­jec­tor, Golden Mile Tower, 6001 Beach Road</p>
    <p>MRT Ni­coll High­way</p>
    <p>WHEN To­day to Sun­day AD­MIS­SION $15 stan­dard</p>
    <p>INFO the­p­ro­jec­tor.sg</p>

